We currently offer one class as a PSF, the `GaussianPSF`. The fitted parameters are sigma, amplitude and (x,y) position. In the end, we don't care about the amplitude, only about the total flux (given by the integral and depending on amplitude and sigma).
I have a feeling that there must be an analytic expression for this, but I'm right now a little confused by the fact that the docs https://github.com/astropy/photutils/blob/master/photutils/psf.py#L210 and the code https://github.com/astropy/photutils/blob/master/photutils/psf.py#L261 use a different normalisation and neither of them is `2/sqrt(pi)` as I expected it to be http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Error_function.

